-- CANADA STOCKS-TSX little changed as Scotiabank gains offset by miners
-- By John Tilak
-- Tue May 27, 2014 09:38AM EDT
-- None



TORONTO, May 27 (Reuters) - Canada's main stock index was little changed on Tuesday, with a rise in shares of Bank of Nova Scotia <BNS.TO> following the lender's quarterly results offset by weakness in the gold-mining sector after the bullion price declined.

